<!--e57a25ab6845829454e8d69fc972939a-->

The following sections might be updated with supplementary metadata relevant to reviewers and maintainers.

<!--174a7506f384e20aa4161008e828411d-->
### Conflicts
Reviewers, this pull request conflicts with the following ones:

* [#25797](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/25797) (build: Add CMake-based build system by hebasto)

If you consider this pull request important, please also help to review the conflicting pull requests. Ideally, start with the one that should be merged first.
Updated the PR description with Guix build hashes.

I wonder if it might be better to just drop minisketch until there's something actually using it.

We've built it as part of two major releases now, without any actual use...

> I wonder if it might be better to just drop minisketch until there's something actually using it.

At this point, that seems like more hassle than just leaving it as-is. Having it in tree is convenient for PRs like #21515 (and it's children), and the overhead of having it in the tree, is basically 0.
